    <text>
        <front>
            <div type="editorial_desc">
                <p>In this cartoon commentary on the end of the Civil War, vice president Andrew Johnson sits atop a large globe displaying a map of the United States with a tear running down the middle. Using scissors and a needle and thread, Johnson attempts to stitch the map together. To the right, Abraham Lincoln uses a fence rail to stabilize the globe and offers words of encouragement to Johnson. On the ground to the left of the globe sit a ruler or gauge and a spool of thread.</p>
            </div>
        </front>

